%N A393393 Array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of squares reachable in k (but no fewer) leaps of an (r,s)-leaper on an infinite chessboard, where r = A094192(n-1) and s = A094193(n-1) if n > 1, (r,s) = (1,0) if n = 1; n, k >= 1.
%C A393393 Row n is the coordination sequence for the infinite (r,s)-leaper graph.
%C A393393 For n >= 1, (r,s) runs through all pairs of nonnegative integers, in lexicographic order, satisfying r > s and GCD(r+s,r-s) = 1. The latter condition ensures that the underlying infinite (r,s)-leaper graph is connected.
%F A393393 T(n,k) = A008412(k) if k < r+s.
